<subSubSection id="C339651DFFDCEF1AA1AB6E45FBD6C982" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9C3696FFDCEF1AA1AB6E45FBD6C982" blockId="2.[151,1437,1357,1779]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B957EA84FFDCEF1AA1AB6E45FEACCA16" bold="true" box="[151,273,1357,1382]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae 8-segmented, segments III–IV (
<figureCitation id="13182A13FFDCEF1AA3C46E45FC81CA16" box="[760,828,1357,1382]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[173,1416,193,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1417,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–9. The paired number on the photos indicates the character states. (2) Parascolothrips priesneri antennal segments II–VII; (3) Bradinothrips musae antennal segments II–VI; (4) Bradinothrips musae meso- and metasternum; (5) Parascolothrips priesneri meso- and metasternum; (6) Parascolothrips priesneri pronotum, meso- and metanotum; (7) Caliothrips tongi head, Character 5 was pointed on ocellar triangle, and character 6 on postocular area; (8) Parascolothrips priesneri sternites VI–VII; (9) Echinothrips americanus tergite V. (10) Dictyothrips betae tergite VI." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2656510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) with forked sense cones, segment IV with one long extra sense cone. Head wider than long, reticulate only behind eyes, ocellar setae I absent; ocellar triangle smooth; at least one pair of postocular setae longer than others; maxillary palps 2-segmented. Pronotum wider than long, sculpture weak or absent, two pairs of long posteroangular setae. Mesonotum reticulate, CPS (campaniform sensilla) absent. Metanotum strongly reticulate, median setae behind anterior margin. Only mesosternum (
<figureCitation id="13182A13FFDCEF1AA4736ED5FA29CA86" box="[1359,1428,1501,1526]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[173,1416,193,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1417,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–9. The paired number on the photos indicates the character states. (2) Parascolothrips priesneri antennal segments II–VII; (3) Bradinothrips musae antennal segments II–VI; (4) Bradinothrips musae meso- and metasternum; (5) Parascolothrips priesneri meso- and metasternum; (6) Parascolothrips priesneri pronotum, meso- and metanotum; (7) Caliothrips tongi head, Character 5 was pointed on ocellar triangle, and character 6 on postocular area; (8) Parascolothrips priesneri sternites VI–VII; (9) Echinothrips americanus tergite V. (10) Dictyothrips betae tergite VI." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2656510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with spinula, metasternum furca (
<figureCitation id="13182A13FFDCEF1AA3266D0AFDDDC96A" box="[538,608,1538,1563]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[173,1416,193,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1417,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–9. The paired number on the photos indicates the character states. (2) Parascolothrips priesneri antennal segments II–VII; (3) Bradinothrips musae antennal segments II–VI; (4) Bradinothrips musae meso- and metasternum; (5) Parascolothrips priesneri meso- and metasternum; (6) Parascolothrips priesneri pronotum, meso- and metanotum; (7) Caliothrips tongi head, Character 5 was pointed on ocellar triangle, and character 6 on postocular area; (8) Parascolothrips priesneri sternites VI–VII; (9) Echinothrips americanus tergite V. (10) Dictyothrips betae tergite VI." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2656510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) enlarged but not reaching to mesosternum. Fore wing first and second veins with incomplete setal rows; clavus with 1 veinal setae but without discal setae; posterior fringe cilia wavy. Tarsi 2-segmented. Abdominal tergites with broad entire craspedum; microtrichia and ctenidia absent; tergite VIII without posteromarginal comb; tergite IX with only posterior CPS. Sternites also with broad entire craspedum; sternites II–VII with three pairs of posteromarginal setae; sternite VII with two pairs of extra setae and all posteromarginal setae submarginal. Male without sternal pore plates or with one minute (
<quantity id="4CDB9B73FFDCEF1AA5906DBDFAAAC9BE" box="[1196,1303,1717,1742]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" unit="�m" value="5.0">5 micron</quantity>
) pore plate medially on sternite VII or sternites VI and VII, tergite IX with two pairs of stout setae.
</paragraph>
